Digital Insurance Platform Developer Learning Journey

This learning journey is for anyone in a technical role with a focus in the insurance industries. The journey will guide you through all of the Salesforce Industries product training courses and certifications that are needed to prepare you to work on a Digital Insurance Platform implementation project.

Step 1: Get Started with the Digital Insurance Platform
Before You Begin, earn the Salesforce Administrator Credential and the Salesforce Platform App Builder Credential.
Get Started with the Digital Insurance Platform
Digital Insurance Platform Foundations
Digital Insurance Platform Demo
Claims Management Demo

Learn Insurance Foundations:
The Insurance Industry
Insurance Quoting Foundations
Individual Insurance Policy Administration Foundations
Group Insurance Contracts and Enrollments Foundations
Insurance Claims Foundations
Insurance Data Model

Step 2: Learn OmniStudio
Use OmniStudio tools to rapidly build and deploy digital-first customer experiences across channels.
Get Trained: Build Guided Experiences with OmniStudio or take Expert-Led Class OMS435
Study and Prepare: OmniStudio Developer Exam Guide and Trailmix
Get Certified!: Schedule Your OmniStudio Developer Exam

Step 3: Learn Quote, Rate, and Apply
Rapidly build digital insurance quoting experiences.
Get Trained: Get to Know Insurance Quoting, Discover and Build Quoting Experiences for Insurance
Master Product Modeling: Design Product Models for Insurance Applications

Step 4: Learn Policies, Enrollments, and Claims
Discover how to build and manage end-to-end policy, enrollment, and claim management processes.
Learn Policy Administration: Individual Insurance Policy Administration Foundations
Build OmniScripts for Individual Insurance Policy Administration
Learn Claims Management: Insurance Claims Foundations
Build and Manage Claims for Insurance

Step 5: Keep Learning!
Keep growing your Digital Insurance Developer skills with additional training:
Learn about the Digital Insurance Application Suites
Learn about CLM and Document Generation
Learn More About OmniStudio, Business Rules Engine
